Task 3: CSS Selectors

Definition and Usage: CSS selectors are used to target specific HTML elements based on their tags, classes, IDs, attributes, or pseudo-classes.
Example:
HTML

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>CSS Selectors</title>
    <style>
        p {
            color: green;
        }

        .special {
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        #heading {
            text-align: center;
        }

        [href] {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }

        a:hover {
            color: red;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1 id="heading">Heading</h1>
    <p>This is a regular paragraph.</p>
    <p class="special">This is a special paragraph.</p>
    <a href="https://example.com">Link</a>
</body>
</html>

- Explanation:
      - p: Targets all paragraph elements.
      - .special: Targets elements with the class "special".
      - #heading: Targets the element with the ID "heading".
      - [href]: Targets elements with the attribute "href".
      - a:hover: Targets anchor elements when hovered over.